{"body": "Invasive candidiasis remains one of the most serious community and healthcare-acquired infections worldwide. Conventional Candida detection methods based on blood and plate culture are time-consuming and require at least 2-4 days to identify various Candida species. Despite considerable advances for candidiasis detection, the development of simple, compact and portable point-of-care diagnostics for rapid and precise testing that automatically performs cell lysis, nucleic acid extraction, purification and detection still remains a challenge. Here, we systematically review most prominent conventional and nonconventional techniques for the detection of various Candida species, including Candida staining, blood culture, serological testing and nucleic acid-based analysis. We also discuss the most advanced lab on a chip devices for candida detection.\n", "embeddings": ["-0.1886366", "0.39451265", "1.5803292", "0.09570625", "0.45087758", "-0.5185327", "0.19443981", "0.053125195", "0.09952743", "0.098430276", "-0.40838242", "-0.6602718", "0.76102775", "0.67918485", "-0.9363242", "-0.2718439", "0.24829109", "0.31869885", "-0.44397256", "-1.6883041", "-0.38257247", "-2.400488", "-0.21061186", "-0.14864257", "-1.0057508", "-0.40931854", "1.6226829", "0.18740265", "-1.8649248", "0.12676531", "0.9269112", "-0.7758757", "-0.96253115", "0.66618997", "0.3042428", "0.02495237", "-0.4879917", "-0.03850736", "0.0025337283", "-0.23578234", "0.57973844", "-1.1835077", "0.81034815", "-0.5098288", "1.1297454", "0.06443065", "-0.83335155", "-1.0233424", "0.05694883", "-0.15851024", "0.67069787", "1.4221545", "-0.040729977", "-0.76141584", "-0.4129022", "-0.9456918", "0.18444285", "0.68423164", "-0.81058735", "-0.44775027", "-0.053340346", "0.1939088", "0.99167466", "0.43085986", "-1.1626443", "0.48863322", "1.3539861", "1.1708761", "-0.42249858", "0.80507225", "-1.3065628", "-0.1764762", "0.34535035", "-0.24182414", "-0.2390745", "0.33071542", "-0.34741405", "0.19028229", "-0.24